        <div class="eyebrow">HOW IT WORKS</div>
        <h2>Built like an operating system, not a landing page promise.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="operating-grid">
        <article class="operating-card tall">
          <div class="card-index">01</div>
          <h3>Launch the brief</h3>
          <p>Define what needs to move: a song, brand, product, launch, challenge or message. Clipency gives that objective structure before distribution begins.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="operating-card">
          <div class="card-index">02</div>
          <h3>Activate creators</h3>
          <p>Creators participate through campaigns designed around output, not inflated promises.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="operating-card">
          <div class="card-index">03</div>
          <h3>Collect proof</h3>
          <p>Every submission can be reviewed through links, status, views and approval data.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="operating-card">
          <div class="card-index">04</div>
          <h3>Track performance</h3>
          <p>Campaigns become visible through submissions, views, earnings and payouts.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="operating-card wide">
          <div class="card-index">05</div>
          <h3>Repeat what works</h3>
          <p>Once performance patterns appear, brands can scale what moves attention instead of guessing what might work.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

